p.s. I will also post this in the server health is excellent thread <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukratekitris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krate Kitris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 5:58:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> I don't think the server is dying, but I do actually think it could use some help.<br>
<br>
1- TLC.  This needs to go for quest items only.  It is very hard when you are low level (1-10) and don't know much about the game and are still making friends to find out that you missed out on nice little quests.  It is also frustrating that by just doing some of the newer quests from the start you out level them and cant finish.  This IS after all EverQUEST, so why make quests harder or more frustrating.  My idea of fun is not trolling Alacahoweveryouspellit or EQstratics or Everlore to find out exactly when I can do what and where I need to do it.  I do like TLC for things like stopping high level farms and things of that nature.  But for Christ sake lay off killing some of these quests with TLC.<br>
<br>
2- Language Barriar.  This is perfect.  There is no reason a Troll should be able to speak to a Halfling without lots and lots of learning.  Why should they.<br>
<br>
3- Shout/Auction/OOC.  All shout shout work just like it is now.  Do you really think if you yelled at one end of SK someone should be able to hear it at the other?  Auction should only work in cities as it does now.  OOC I always hated, glad its gone.  <br>
<br>
4- About finding groups and anon.  I sort of like that.  You should have to wander about to find people to ask for a group.  As far as anon goes, you should not be able to do a /who and get class and level.  You should however be able to get just level.  Or if someone is /LFG when you do a /who LFG you get their name and level.  Who cares what class they are, if they need a group, you need more and their the same level then let them play (unless your all OG and they are OE or something).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Get rid of the QUEST TLC and make it a tad easier to find someone LFG your level and that would help the most I think while still keeping the 133T d00d2 ()()f |&lt;|_|z j00 50&gt;&lt;0X0R2<br>
 out of the game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 8:19:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;Then ker-plunk yourself into the middle of a rainforest. Look around. See anyone? Not too likely.&gt;&gt;<br>
